WEBVTT

00:20.187 --> 00:21.772
<i>It's Clara.
I'm not in.</i>

00:21.772 --> 00:23.858
<i>Leave me a message.</i>

00:23.858 --> 00:25.860
<i>Clara, it's me again.</i>

00:25.860 --> 00:28.446
<i>I'm just calling to see...</i>

00:28.446 --> 00:30.364
if you'd pick up.

00:34.660 --> 00:36.662
I miss you.

00:45.254 --> 00:47.590
Today is a momentous day...

00:47.590 --> 00:51.719
a historic day as former German
Chancellor Adolf Hitler...

00:51.719 --> 00:55.222
...is set to be tried for crimes
against humanity...

00:55.222 --> 00:57.349
...by an International
Criminal Tribunal.

00:58.768 --> 01:00.227
 <i>It is
the culmination</i>

01:00.227 --> 01:01.604
of a surreal two months

01:01.604 --> 01:03.397
<i>in which dental records</i>

01:03.397 --> 01:05.733
<i>and fingerprints have
proved the veracity of...</i>

01:05.733 --> 01:07.359
Investigations have been opened

01:07.359 --> 01:09.987
as to how Hitler...

01:09.987 --> 01:14.825
...was able to stage
his own death and evade justice.

01:14.825 --> 01:16.619
It is
believed that a group of...

01:16.619 --> 01:19.205
...undercover "Nazi hunters"
were involved...

01:19.205 --> 01:20.748
...in bringing Mr. Hitler
to justice.

01:20.748 --> 01:24.126
Only one member of the group
has been publicly identified.

01:24.126 --> 01:27.171
<i>The woman who single-handedly
walked Adolf Hitler</i>

01:27.171 --> 01:29.924
into the American Embassy
in Uruguay.

01:29.924 --> 01:31.550
Former
FBI Agent...

01:31.550 --> 01:33.511
Former agent
of the American FBI...

01:33.511 --> 01:35.346
- Millicent Morris.
- Millicent Morris.

01:35.346 --> 01:36.639
Will you tell us
how you caught him?

01:36.639 --> 01:37.723
Who else were you working with?

01:37.723 --> 01:38.808
Do you want to see him hanged?

01:38.808 --> 01:39.975
Should Hitler be put to death?

02:31.360 --> 02:33.112
Hey, you okay?

02:36.991 --> 02:40.536
I wish my Murray
was here to see this.

02:45.958 --> 02:47.960
He is here.

02:49.211 --> 02:51.088
He's seeing this.

03:01.974 --> 03:04.268
<i>He owns a toy shop
in Manhattan?</i>

03:04.268 --> 03:05.811
<i>Yes,
Heinz Richter opened</i>

03:05.811 --> 03:08.314
The Red Balloon Toy Shop
20 years ago.

03:08.314 --> 03:10.024
He lives alone in Forest Hills.

03:10.024 --> 03:12.067
They... we're very close.

03:12.067 --> 03:14.194
But we need more.

03:14.194 --> 03:16.238
- More?
- Yes, we need more.

03:16.238 --> 03:19.283
We need to be 100% certain.

03:19.283 --> 03:22.244
- Oh, but Ruth...
- No, she's right. He...

03:22.244 --> 03:24.538
He's a collector, this man.

03:24.538 --> 03:26.290
He has something

03:26.290 --> 03:28.375
of his former life with him.

03:28.375 --> 03:30.461
I can assure you that.

03:31.962 --> 03:33.756
Break in.

03:33.756 --> 03:35.966
- See what you find.
- Meyer, that could expose us.

03:35.966 --> 03:37.551
Killing an innocent man?

03:37.551 --> 03:40.763
That will expose us to things
we could never recover from.

03:41.972 --> 03:44.808
We're very close here,
but you must verify.

03:44.808 --> 03:47.895
I will see what I can do.

03:49.188 --> 03:50.230
Good.

03:53.067 --> 03:55.069
Ah, yes.

03:56.862 --> 03:59.406
After all these years...

03:59.406 --> 04:02.660
to think that we may have
finally found him is...

04:02.660 --> 04:05.120
Look what we created.

04:07.289 --> 04:09.458
It's great.

04:09.458 --> 04:13.253
It's not the only thing
we created, Meyer.

04:14.505 --> 04:17.841
She was a beautiful girl,

04:17.841 --> 04:20.469
- Naomi.
- My mother's name.

04:20.469 --> 04:23.931
Your mother was a saint.

04:23.931 --> 04:25.975
So...

04:25.975 --> 04:28.268
so I thought it would rub off.

04:29.311 --> 04:33.107
But she was a pain the ass. Naomi.

04:33.107 --> 04:35.943
Precocious, bold.

04:35.943 --> 04:37.486
Like her mother.

04:37.486 --> 04:40.906
But she was also
like her father.

04:40.906 --> 04:43.409
She was kind, good.

04:43.409 --> 04:48.622
I wish...
oh, I wish you met her.

04:48.622 --> 04:51.542
Oh, I... I wish I did, too.

04:53.043 --> 04:54.837
Look at me, Meyer.

04:54.837 --> 04:56.839
Look.

04:56.839 --> 04:59.758
She had your eyes.

05:01.260 --> 05:03.262
Yeah.

05:04.763 --> 05:06.765
I...

05:15.858 --> 05:18.027
I remember.

05:18.027 --> 05:21.363
When he did this to you
in that awful room.

05:21.363 --> 05:24.700
I could feel it, too, I suppose.

05:24.700 --> 05:27.119
Seared...

05:27.119 --> 05:29.121
on my own heart.

05:30.539 --> 05:32.791
So many scars, Ruth.

05:32.791 --> 05:34.376
Hmm?

05:34.376 --> 05:36.253
Yes.

05:36.253 --> 05:38.422
What are we but scars?

05:44.762 --> 05:46.847
I'm so glad...

05:48.682 --> 05:50.809
...that I found you.

05:53.312 --> 05:55.606
Finally...

05:55.606 --> 05:58.525
I've found you.

07:23.152 --> 07:25.946
Let him live! Let him live!

07:25.946 --> 07:28.407
Security is on high alert

07:28.407 --> 07:30.784
at the Munich courthouse.

07:30.784 --> 07:33.203
Germany has received
credible threats...

07:33.203 --> 07:37.082
...of a possible terror attack
from white supremacist groups.

07:37.082 --> 07:39.585
An emotional day is expected...

07:39.585 --> 07:40.669
...as spectators
include survivors

07:40.669 --> 07:41.962
of the Nazi concentration camps.

07:41.962 --> 07:44.047
Gosh, he looks old.

07:46.842 --> 07:48.844
Yeah.

07:48.844 --> 07:50.262
Authorities are afraid

07:50.262 --> 07:51.805
of an attack.

07:51.805 --> 07:54.600
And they should be afraid.

07:59.146 --> 08:00.480
Showtime.

08:15.537 --> 08:18.123
 <i>Hitler will
be tried by five justices:</i>

08:18.123 --> 08:21.793
<i>Boris Federov of Russia,
Marion Jenneret of France,</i>

08:21.793 --> 08:24.338
<i>Archibald Hollings
of Great Britain,</i>

08:24.338 --> 08:26.465
<i>Lorraine Collins of the U.S.,</i>

08:26.465 --> 08:29.593
<i>and Chief Justice
Wolfgang Müeller of Germany,</i>

08:29.593 --> 08:32.304
<i>whose objectivity
has come into question</i>

08:32.304 --> 08:35.432
due to his alleged ties to the
Nazi regime as a law student.

08:35.432 --> 08:38.143
Justice Müeller
has not commented

08:38.143 --> 08:39.978
- on the allegations.
<i>- We are gathered here</i>

08:39.978 --> 08:42.397
for the International
War Crimes Tribunal

08:42.397 --> 08:43.523
in the name of the people

08:43.523 --> 08:44.775
in the criminal case

08:44.775 --> 08:46.360
against Adolf Hitler.

08:46.360 --> 08:48.695
Many have declared this case

08:48.695 --> 08:50.405
to be the trial
of the millennium.

08:50.405 --> 08:53.659
I would offer
that in this courtroom,

08:53.659 --> 08:56.286
with this agent of the court
presiding over it,

08:56.286 --> 08:59.206
this will be a trial
like any other.

08:59.206 --> 09:02.042
We are simply here
to establish this individual's

09:02.042 --> 09:04.836
innocence or guilt
beyond a reasonable doubt

09:04.836 --> 09:07.256
of the crimes
of which he is accused.

09:08.257 --> 09:11.260
Remember, my fellow justices
and I must arrive

09:11.260 --> 09:13.595
at a unanimous decision
before the ruling

09:13.595 --> 09:15.430
is considered final.

09:17.975 --> 09:21.645
Mr. Frankel,
it's the prosecution's case.

09:26.483 --> 09:28.652
Though it is no exaggeration
to say that our case has been

09:28.652 --> 09:32.114
a Herculean task--

09:32.114 --> 09:35.909
to tally the grave offenses
of the accused...

09:37.536 --> 09:39.538
...Adolf Hitler.

09:41.957 --> 09:43.959
The fact is...

09:43.959 --> 09:46.211
our case is
a relatively simple one.

09:46.211 --> 09:48.547
Given the work
of our predecessors

09:48.547 --> 09:50.382
and the precedent established

09:50.382 --> 09:52.551
by the International
Military Tribunal at Nuremberg

09:52.551 --> 09:54.136
and the subsequent trials
in the period

09:54.136 --> 09:55.721
immediately after the war.

09:55.721 --> 09:57.639
It is therefore our contention

09:57.639 --> 10:00.142
that we will present to you...

10:01.852 --> 10:03.979
...an open and shut,

10:03.979 --> 10:06.064
airtight case.

10:10.068 --> 10:13.280
Thank you,
Mr. Frankel.

10:13.280 --> 10:17.075
The defense may now rise
and state

10:17.075 --> 10:19.411
their case.

10:19.411 --> 10:21.788
Knock 'em dead.

10:27.627 --> 10:30.672
Traitor. Traitor!

10:30.672 --> 10:34.217
Traitor!

10:34.217 --> 10:36.136
You're a Jew!

10:36.136 --> 10:37.637
- How can you represent him?
- Order!
There will be order.

10:37.637 --> 10:40.015
Your Honors.

10:40.015 --> 10:42.184
I, um...

10:42.184 --> 10:45.312
I stand before you

10:45.312 --> 10:49.107
on behalf of my client,
Adolf Hitler.

10:49.107 --> 10:51.860
And, um...

10:51.860 --> 10:54.404
I...

10:56.907 --> 10:59.117
I am not here to argue

10:59.117 --> 11:00.535
that...

11:00.535 --> 11:02.662
my client is not a monster.

11:02.662 --> 11:05.248
That he wasn't a dictator

11:05.248 --> 11:08.460
or even a murderer.

11:08.460 --> 11:12.130
I am here to defend his right

11:12.130 --> 11:15.425
to a free and fair trial.

11:15.425 --> 11:18.220
And I am here...

11:18.220 --> 11:20.847
to argue that Adolf Hitler...

11:20.847 --> 11:23.058
should be found not guilty

11:23.058 --> 11:25.143
of the specific charges
he is accused of.

11:29.564 --> 11:31.566
Thank you.

11:33.360 --> 11:34.569
Let us proceed.

11:34.569 --> 11:35.821
<i>Please,</i>

11:35.821 --> 11:38.115
tell us your occupation,
Mr. Speer,

11:38.115 --> 11:40.826
between 1942 and 1945.

11:42.035 --> 11:45.414
I served the Reich as minister
of armaments and war production.

11:47.666 --> 11:50.335
This is an affidavit,
which you signed in Munich.

11:51.253 --> 11:53.213
Would you please read the

11:53.213 --> 11:54.631
highlighted section
to the court.

11:58.635 --> 12:01.555
"Hatred of the Jews was Hitler's

12:01.555 --> 12:04.933
"motor and central point.

12:04.933 --> 12:08.395
"Perhaps even the very element
that motivated him.

12:08.395 --> 12:12.441
"I was present at
the session of the Reichstag

12:12.441 --> 12:14.901
"of 30th January 1939,

12:14.901 --> 12:17.904
"when Hitler assured us

12:17.904 --> 12:20.782
"that in case of a war,

12:20.782 --> 12:23.201
"not the Germans,

12:23.201 --> 12:25.871
but the Jews
would be annihilated."

12:25.871 --> 12:28.373
Tell me,
when did you first learn

12:28.373 --> 12:30.125
of Adolf Hitler's plan
to exterminate

12:30.125 --> 12:31.543
Europe's Jewish population?

12:31.543 --> 12:33.920
Uh, Objection, Your Honors. Leading.

12:33.920 --> 12:35.797
Objection sustained.

12:35.797 --> 12:37.674
I'll move on.

12:37.674 --> 12:40.677
In 1945, Hitler issued
his so-called Nero Decree.

12:40.677 --> 12:42.762
What did this policy call for?

12:42.762 --> 12:45.765
Anything of value
within Reich territory

12:45.765 --> 12:47.642
that could be used by the enemy

12:47.642 --> 12:49.686
for the prosecution of the war

12:49.686 --> 12:52.481
was to be destroyed.

12:52.481 --> 12:54.608
And why did he issue this order?

12:54.608 --> 12:56.109
Objection, Your Honors.

12:56.109 --> 12:57.736
- Speculation.
- Sustained.

12:57.736 --> 12:59.279
Your Honors, this witness
will have insight into

12:59.279 --> 13:00.572
- the reasoning behind...
- I've ruled.

13:01.656 --> 13:04.034
Move along, Counsel.

13:06.203 --> 13:07.746
Tell me.

13:07.746 --> 13:10.165
When you last saw Adolf Hitler

13:10.165 --> 13:12.375
in his bunker in Berlin,

13:12.375 --> 13:14.377
what did he say to you?

13:14.377 --> 13:15.795
He said...

13:17.297 --> 13:19.508
...his biggest regret
was that he hadn't

13:19.508 --> 13:22.135
finished off the Jews.

13:24.012 --> 13:26.848
And why do you think
that was his biggest regret?

13:26.848 --> 13:29.226
Objection, Your Honors.
Again, speculation.

13:29.226 --> 13:31.853
- Objection sustained.
- Your honors, it is
perfectly within the...

13:31.853 --> 13:34.105
- I said sustained.
- ...perfectly within
the prosecution's right

13:34.105 --> 13:36.233
- to question the witness
in this way!
- I said sustained, Counsel!

13:36.233 --> 13:38.818
Mm, you did.

13:40.403 --> 13:42.656
Bullshit.

13:44.115 --> 13:47.369
Counsels, in our chambers.

13:49.120 --> 13:50.956
Beg your pardon,
but are you gonna allow me

13:50.956 --> 13:52.624
to get more than
a question in before sustaining

13:52.624 --> 13:55.043
some errant,
extralegal objection?

13:57.254 --> 13:58.838
Are you finished?

14:01.174 --> 14:03.260
Yes.

14:03.260 --> 14:05.345
Your Honors.

14:05.345 --> 14:06.805
I'd like to
remind you, Counsel,

14:06.805 --> 14:08.682
that the burden of proof
in this case

14:08.682 --> 14:11.476
falls on you.

14:11.476 --> 14:13.853
You must firmly establish
Hitler's culpability

14:13.853 --> 14:16.648
for crimes against peace,
war crimes,

14:16.648 --> 14:19.067
crimes against humanity,
and conspiracy

14:19.067 --> 14:21.486
to commit
those foregoing crimes.

14:21.486 --> 14:24.197
The charges that you brought.

14:24.197 --> 14:26.616
Now, if you can do this,
beyond a reasonable doubt,

14:26.616 --> 14:29.035
then I shall rule in your favor.

14:29.035 --> 14:32.497
But if you can't,
I shall rule in his.

14:33.540 --> 14:36.418
It's as simple as that.

14:36.418 --> 14:39.546
Am I understood, Mr. Frankel?

14:40.797 --> 14:41.840
Yes.

14:41.840 --> 14:44.092
Good.

15:00.775 --> 15:03.528
Just doing my job.

15:03.528 --> 15:05.697
Doing the right thing.

15:09.117 --> 15:11.077
We're both Jewish, you and I,
and, yet, I suppose

15:11.077 --> 15:14.456
we have a very different idea
of what the "right thing" is.

15:17.626 --> 15:21.171
<i>We now move to call to the stand
the survivors of the Holocaust.</i>

15:21.171 --> 15:23.423
The court must move past
the abstraction

15:23.423 --> 15:26.384
of genocide and hear it

15:26.384 --> 15:28.219
from the victims themselves.

15:28.219 --> 15:29.846
You may proceed, Mr. Frankel.

15:29.846 --> 15:31.556
I now call to the stand

15:31.556 --> 15:33.433
Mrs. Mindy Markowitz

15:33.433 --> 15:35.393
of Brooklyn, New York,

15:35.393 --> 15:37.479
by way of Kalisz, Poland.

15:37.479 --> 15:41.191
<i>Would you please
state your name for the court?</i>

15:43.234 --> 15:46.696
Mindy Markowitz.

15:46.696 --> 15:48.823
Abraham Putnitsky.

15:48.823 --> 15:50.825
Esther Schwartzman.

15:50.825 --> 15:52.535
Vadoma Orsos.

15:52.535 --> 15:53.787
Isaac Wolff.

15:53.787 --> 15:55.622
Sara Weil.

15:55.622 --> 15:58.291
Would you tell us
where you were born?

15:58.291 --> 16:01.586
Kalisz, Poland.

16:01.586 --> 16:02.879
Berlin, Germany.

16:02.879 --> 16:05.382
Ostrava, Czechoslovakia.

16:05.382 --> 16:08.301
Zalaegerszeg, Hungary.

16:08.301 --> 16:09.386
Vienna, Austria.

16:09.386 --> 16:11.054
Lodz, Poland.

16:11.054 --> 16:12.806
Could you please tell us

16:12.806 --> 16:15.016
what happened to you

16:15.016 --> 16:17.644
under the Nazi regime?

16:20.689 --> 16:22.732
The gestapo

16:22.732 --> 16:24.859
took us from

16:24.859 --> 16:27.779
our small apartment...

16:27.779 --> 16:31.408
and forced us onto cattle cars.

16:31.408 --> 16:33.743
- Objection, Your Honors.
- What?

16:33.743 --> 16:36.621
On what grounds, Counselor?

16:36.621 --> 16:39.874
I am deeply sorry
for what Mrs...

16:39.874 --> 16:42.293
Markowitz has gone through,
but I object

16:42.293 --> 16:44.546
on the grounds of relevancy.

16:44.546 --> 16:46.715
Your Honors.

16:46.715 --> 16:49.592
At a time when the truth

16:49.592 --> 16:52.053
about the Holocaust
is frequently

16:52.053 --> 16:53.972
and fervently denied...

16:53.972 --> 16:56.224
belittled

16:56.224 --> 16:58.476
and whitewashed...

16:58.476 --> 16:59.978
it is important to establish

16:59.978 --> 17:01.938
the fundamental truth

17:01.938 --> 17:04.816
that the Holocaust happened.

17:04.816 --> 17:08.820
That it was a systematic
campaign of genocide

17:08.820 --> 17:11.072
by actors and nations--

17:11.072 --> 17:14.284
many of whom wish it could
be written off as a fantasy--

17:14.284 --> 17:17.120
that resulted in the deaths

17:17.120 --> 17:19.539
of 11 million

17:19.539 --> 17:21.499
men, women

17:21.499 --> 17:23.877
and children.

17:25.712 --> 17:27.630
And was conceived and executed

17:27.630 --> 17:29.799
by the man who sits

17:29.799 --> 17:31.885
in that glass box.

17:33.636 --> 17:36.055
If these survivors' testimony
of their experience

17:36.055 --> 17:39.476
is not relevant, Your Honors...

17:39.476 --> 17:42.687
well, I don't know what is.

17:44.189 --> 17:46.065
Overruled.

17:46.065 --> 17:48.485
You may proceed,

17:48.485 --> 17:50.779
Mrs. Markowitz.

17:52.071 --> 17:54.324
There... there were dozens of us

17:54.324 --> 17:56.701
in the cattle car.

17:56.701 --> 17:59.579
No room to sit
or go to the bathroom.

17:59.579 --> 18:01.790
Hardly any air.

18:01.790 --> 18:04.209
The Nazi guard shot my father

18:04.209 --> 18:06.753
right in front of me.

18:06.753 --> 18:09.047
My mother, too.

18:09.047 --> 18:11.216
And then he laughed.

18:11.216 --> 18:12.926
"Left, right."

18:13.968 --> 18:16.054
That's what the Nazi guard said.

18:16.054 --> 18:17.180
They marched her

18:17.180 --> 18:20.099
right into the gas chambers.

18:20.099 --> 18:21.559
We saw

18:21.559 --> 18:24.312
the awful black smoke

18:24.312 --> 18:25.688
coming from the crematoria.

18:25.688 --> 18:26.940
<i>She was</i>

18:26.940 --> 18:29.067
seven years old.

18:30.527 --> 18:32.487
My daughter.

18:32.487 --> 18:35.698
My boyfriend and I were forced
to go on a death march.

18:35.698 --> 18:38.368
Half-naked, emaciated.

18:38.368 --> 18:40.745
Snow falling on our heads

18:40.745 --> 18:43.081
as we heard the allied gunfire
from the distance.

18:43.081 --> 18:44.332
<i>The guards</i>

18:44.332 --> 18:46.251
assigned me the role

18:46.251 --> 18:49.379
of loading the dead bodies

18:49.379 --> 18:52.215
into a mass grave.

18:54.467 --> 18:57.262
I couldn't bear it,

18:57.262 --> 18:59.639
so I ran away.

19:03.184 --> 19:06.604
He was a beautiful boy.

19:07.689 --> 19:09.065
Aaron.

19:10.984 --> 19:13.528
When we got to the camps...

19:13.528 --> 19:16.281
the Nazis tried

19:16.281 --> 19:18.449
to separate us.

19:21.244 --> 19:23.705
My husband, Murray...

19:23.705 --> 19:26.875
wouldn't let go of Aaron.

19:28.543 --> 19:31.254
The Nazi guard...

19:32.422 --> 19:35.049
...r-ripped Aaron

19:35.049 --> 19:38.011
from Murray's arms...

19:38.011 --> 19:41.055
and shot my little boy

19:41.055 --> 19:43.433
<i>in the chest.</i>

19:45.101 --> 19:48.229
I miss him every day.

19:49.522 --> 19:51.107
I miss my Murray, too.

19:51.107 --> 19:52.817
<i>Mein velt.</i>

19:52.817 --> 19:55.904
How life
would have been different

19:55.904 --> 19:58.698
if not for all this.

20:01.701 --> 20:03.870
If not for you.

20:06.873 --> 20:09.834
I have long dreamt of this day.

20:09.834 --> 20:11.920
The day...

20:13.338 --> 20:15.465
...when I would face you...

