48:18.646 --> 48:20.982
I can lead them.

48:20.982 --> 48:22.567
They're getting us out of here.

48:22.567 --> 48:24.944
A helicopter's on its way.

48:27.280 --> 48:28.948
Get down! Down!

48:51.596 --> 48:56.017
Travis! Where are you?!

49:15.662 --> 49:18.206
Look at me. Look at me!

49:24.545 --> 49:25.922
Jonah!

49:29.008 --> 49:31.010
Put your fucking guns down! Now!

49:32.136 --> 49:33.388
On the ground!

49:33.388 --> 49:35.848
Get on the fucking ground!

49:35.848 --> 49:38.226
Fuck, fuck, fuck, fuck.

49:38.226 --> 49:40.311
You got to breathe, Jonah.
Hold on.

50:11.676 --> 50:13.636
Get me that fucking ambulance!

50:13.636 --> 50:17.306
Get me an ambulance now!

50:36.284 --> 50:38.870
<i>Ner zeh ani madliq</i>

50:38.870 --> 50:41.122
<i>l'illui nishmat</i>

50:41.122 --> 50:43.666
<i>Re'ut bat Avraham.</i>

50:43.666 --> 50:45.752
Amen.

50:52.091 --> 50:54.427
I wish I knew her.

50:56.971 --> 50:59.599
The real her, you know?

50:59.599 --> 51:02.560
You know the real her, Jonah.

51:02.560 --> 51:04.896
- No. No, I didn't.
- Oh, yes.

51:04.896 --> 51:06.856
Not the...

51:06.856 --> 51:09.484
one who hunted Nazis.

51:10.735 --> 51:12.737
Not the vigilante.

51:14.822 --> 51:16.949
Not the woman
before everything happened.

51:16.949 --> 51:18.868
But you.

51:18.868 --> 51:21.621
You knew all those parts of her.

51:21.621 --> 51:25.166
Well, Jonah, I've been
on this Earth many years.

51:25.166 --> 51:28.628
You know, I have seen
the dimensions of human beings.

51:28.628 --> 51:30.588
I've known the doubles

51:30.588 --> 51:32.423
and the doppelgängers.

51:32.423 --> 51:34.634
Angels and monsters, both.

51:36.511 --> 51:38.513
But above all else...

51:42.600 --> 51:45.102
...there's one true self.

51:45.102 --> 51:47.688
Each of us chooses

51:47.688 --> 51:50.066
who we show that self to.

51:50.066 --> 51:52.276
And Ruth...

51:52.276 --> 51:54.362
chose you.

51:55.738 --> 51:58.574
Only you, Jonah...

51:58.574 --> 52:01.202
saw the real her.

52:01.202 --> 52:03.162
The way she looked at the moon

52:03.162 --> 52:05.122
like it was her friend

52:05.122 --> 52:07.250
who abandoned her
all those years ago.

52:09.460 --> 52:11.462
She always feared that...

52:11.462 --> 52:13.881
she would forget
her mother's face.

52:13.881 --> 52:17.343
I remember she wished
she was not only known

52:17.343 --> 52:18.803
as a survivor.

52:18.803 --> 52:22.431
But she was grateful that,
that-that she did.

52:22.431 --> 52:23.724
She was always grateful.

52:23.724 --> 52:25.643
- Mm.
- So much more to her.

52:25.643 --> 52:27.728
She...

52:27.728 --> 52:30.147
Every time she laughed,
she would wink.

52:30.147 --> 52:32.775
She also loved to wish

52:32.775 --> 52:35.069
on eyelashes.

52:35.069 --> 52:36.946
She loved that.

52:36.946 --> 52:38.823
How wonderful

52:38.823 --> 52:41.576
and liberating for her...

52:41.576 --> 52:43.995
that she had you.

52:43.995 --> 52:47.248
She had you to be there.

52:48.708 --> 52:51.168
And be seen by.

52:51.168 --> 52:53.629
The way you saw her...

52:54.922 --> 52:56.799
As a human being.

52:56.799 --> 52:59.010
And isn't that what we all want?

52:59.010 --> 53:00.720
Hmm?

53:00.720 --> 53:03.389
That think as we may...

53:03.389 --> 53:05.808
otherwise...

53:05.808 --> 53:08.060
